Description: Continuously updated business news, analysis and opinion for broadcast television executives, managers and professionals.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Philadelphia Area, Great Lakes, Northeastern US
Full Description: TVNewsCheck is  believe in TV broadcasting—free, universal, over-the-air broadcasting, where TV got its start and which still offers hertz-for-hertz the best TV programming and public service around. It is their privilege to serve the thousands of individuals who make it happen. From 8 a.m. to 8 p.m. ET, every working day, they deliver news and information for station owners, managers, account executives, programmers, engineers, technicians, anchors, reporters and producers. Like any good newspaper, they closely follow the goings on within their community of TV stations. But they also keep an eye on Washington, the broadcast networks, the advertising marketplace, hardware vendors and—this may be most important—corporate headquarters. And they cover cable, satellite, the Internet and other media, but only because they have an impact on broadcasting. Their focus is always on the TV station. There are already plenty of magazines, newsletters and Web sites that cover TV broadcasting. They do not want to add to the information overload. Their idea is to organize all that is out there, mix in their original reporting and commentary and bring it all together on your desktop with the urgency of all-news radio. The site is designed to give you an up-to-the minute briefing on the dynamic world of TV broadcasting with one top-to-bottom scroll. They read everything so you don't have to. Their promise is that you won't miss a thing if you keep checking in. They are working in a new medium, where the rules change every day, but they are old-fashioned journalists. They want to deliver the news as quickly as they can. They want the scoop. But they also want your trust. They do not sacrifice speed for accuracy. Theydo not report anything unless they have checked it out or made certain it comes from a credible source.

Full Description: Cellanyx is developing the next generation cancer diagnostic. Cancer Diagnostics Patients who are diagnosed with prostate, skin, and breast cancer, are being monitored and/or are surgical candidates will benefit from Cellanyx's technology. Cellanyx's test ordered (at diagnosis) can provide physicians with objective, prognostic information to assist in their treatment decision process.Cellanyx returns two metrics to the practicing physician: the first metric predicts the growth or oncogenic potential of a biopsy, the second metric predicts the metastatic potential of the biopsy. With this information the practicing physician can better assess what treatment plan to pursue. Compound Discovery Cellanyx is also positioned to leverage its technology as a cell-based assay to identify compounds that reduce the growth and metstatic potential of cancer cells, thereby identifying compounds that are less toxic to the body and still effective in slowing down the growth and metastasis of aberrant cancer cells, reverting them, in principal, to a normal state.

Description: Nile is a digital platform that makes it easy for conscientious online shoppers and Black-owned ecommerce brands to connect online.
Headquarters Regions: Washington DC Metro Area, Southern US
Full Description: Nile is a digital platform that makes it easy for conscientious online shoppers and Black-owned ecommerce brands to connect online. Users can employ advanced filtering options to search and browse thousands of Black e-commerce brands on our site, and brands can reach their target audiences with greater ease. The problem Nile solves is two-sided. For conscientious consumers, there is a growing demand to support Black-owned businesses in all aspects, particularly when shopping online. Yet, information about Black brands is disjointed and siloed. Plainly speaking, it’s harder to buy Black than it is to buy from Amazon, so where do consumers end up shopping online? Amazon.  For Black ecommerce brands, the problem is even more pressing. Amongst the vast retail noise on the internet, they can’t find their target customers. Our platform aggregates information about Black brands to make it easy for consumers to find them, and to make it easy for brands to market to interested buyers. Without Nile, users spend more time searching for Black brands on search engines or directories that are focused on local businesses and services, and businesses have a harder time reaching a prime (inter)national audience for their products.
Industry Groups: Commerce and Shopping, Other, Social Impact

Description: Foldable ballet flats that fit in your purse! Matching expandable tote bag for those "killer" heels
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: So, who are the CitySlip-mates behind these funk-tional flats? We’re glad you asked… the CitySlips “story” is one of our favorites!!! Having lived in the city for three years as NYU students, Susie Levitt and Katie Shea were oh-so-familiar with the pain caused by pointy pumps and strappy stilettos. Their love/hate relationship with these fashion icons wasn’t helped by the fact that these petite powerhouses both stand no taller than 5’2”. Despite their suffering, they simply were unwilling to (totally) give up on these beloved wardrobe staples. And yet, corporate internships, subway dashes, dinner dates, the NYC social scene… all of the above led to too many moments of hobbling, near tears, back to their Union Square apartments. The front door never seemed to come soon enough. One too many encounters with shoeless socialites and barefooted babes led to their AH HA moment... CitySlips was born. These entrepreneurial sole-sisters came up with a concept and design that allowed women to carry back-up ballet flats comfortably, compactly, and conveniently. Juggling classroom term papers and corporate term sheets throughout their senior year of college, Susie and Katie enlisted the opinions of friends, the help of NYU professors, and the time of many NYC professionals and mentors. Nine months later (their baby, literally!), they now have a product that is funk-tional, fashionable and affordable! They’re confident that all of you well-heeded women on-the-go will enjoy these fabulous sole savers.
Industry Groups: Clothing and Apparel, Commerce and Shopping, Community and Lifestyle, Design

Description: Logic Pro is a creative tool for professional songwriting, beat-making, editing, and mixing.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Logic Pro is a digital audio workstation software designed by Apple Inc. It's used by music producers, sound designers, and audio engineers to create, edit, and mix music. If you're interested in downloading Logic Pro, there are a few things you need to know first. In this article, we'll cover everything you need to know about Logic Pro download, including system requirements, installation process, features, and more. + System Requirements Before downloading Logic Pro, make sure your Mac meets the system requirements. Logic Pro requires macOS 10.14.6 or later and a Mac with a 64-bit processor. Here are the detailed system requirements: 1. macOS 10.15.7 or later 2. 4GB of RAM (8GB or more recommended) 3. 64-bit processor 4. 1280x768 resolution display or higher 5. 6GB of disk space for a minimum installation or 72GB of disk space for a full Sound Library installation 6. If your Mac doesn't meet these requirements, you won't be able to download and install Logic Pro. + How to Download Logic Pro To download Logic Pro, follow these steps: Go to the Apple website and navigate to the Logic Pro product page. Click on the "Buy" button to purchase Logic Pro. If you already own Logic Pro, skip to step 4. Sign in with your Apple ID and complete the payment process. Open the App Store on your Mac and go to the "Updates" tab. Click on the "Update" button next to Logic Pro to start the download and installation process. + Features of Logic Pro Logic Pro is packed with features that make it one of the best digital audio workstations on the market. Here are some of the standout features: 1. Flex Time and Flex Pitch Flex Time and Flex Pitch allow you to manipulate the timing and pitch of audio recordings. This is especially useful for fixing mistakes or making creative changes to a recording. 2. Drummer Drummer is a virtual session player that can create realistic drum tracks. You can choose from different drummers and styles, and Drummer will automatically generate drum tracks that fit your project. 3. Alchemy Alchemy is a powerful synthesizer that comes with Logic Pro. It has a wide range of sounds and is capable of creating complex textures and evolving soundscapes. 4. Smart Tempo Smart Tempo allows you to record without a click track and automatically match the timing of your recordings to the tempo of your project. This makes it easier to record natural performances without worrying about timing. 5. Logic Remote Logic Remote is an app that allows you to control Logic Pro using your iPad or iPhone. This is useful for recording or mixing from a distance or for controlling Logic Pro while you're away from your Mac.
